SIMPLE: longanberry
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: longanberry
<hw>longanberry</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A tree (<spn>Dimocarpus
longan</spn>) of Southeastern Asia to Australia grown primarily for its
sweet translucent-fleshed edible fruit (the <prod>longan</prod>)
resembling litchi nuts; -- it is sometimes placed in genera
<gen>Euphoria</gen> or <gen>Nephelium</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> longan, lungen, <spn>Dimocarpus longan</spn>,
<spn>Euphoria litchi</spn>, <gen>Nephelium longana</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Asian fruit similar to litchi.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> dragon's eye.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Longanimity</ent>⟦br⟧
